            "@type": "Answer",
            "text": "Larger dogs tend to age faster than smaller dogs. Small dogs reach maturity quickly but then age more slowly, while large and giant breeds have shorter lifespans and age more rapidly after reaching maturity."
          }
        },
        {
          "@type": "Question",
          "name": "What's the difference between dog years and human years?",
